The article discusses the White House's efforts to invest in long-term care and the care workforce, as well as the President's proposal to expand federal support for these services. It highlights the reliance of over seven million seniors and individuals with disabilities on home and community-based services (HCBS), especially during the pandemic. The American Rescue Plan provided significant support to states to strengthen and expand home care programs and better compensate care workers. All 50 states are using this funding to improve their long-term care systems. The article also mentions new data from CMS showing that states have committed about $37 billion in American Rescue Plan funding for HCBS.